  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "While CNNs excel with RGB images, color can sometimes mislead fossil analysis.",
    "Fossils of the same type may differ in color due to variations in mineralogy/composition or staining, with RGB signatures being a poor diagnostic for fossil taxa.",
    "Using binary or grayscale images focuses on morphological features, reducing the risk of misclassification.",
    "This approach ensures more accurate and reliable analysis, especially when color is not a key distinguishing feature.",
    "TL repurposes a model trained for a primary task to a related secondary task, offering advantages in scenarios with scarce labeled data or where training dedicated large models is prohibitively resource-intensive (Lu et al. 2015)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
